    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Macworld Mentions Screenplay Markdown]]></title>
    <link href="http://www.candlerblog.com/2012/01/12/screenplay-markdown-in-macworld/"/>
    <updated>2012-01-12T20:51:00+00:00</updated>
    <id>http://www.candlerblog.com/2012/01/12/screenplay-markdown-in-macworld</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><blockquote><p>As noted above, Marked also supports MultiMarkdown (including math syntax), and screenplay writers may be interested in <a href="http://prolost.com/storage/downloads/spmd/SPMD_proposal.html">Screenplay Markdown</a> and <a href="http://support.markedapp.com/kb/how-to-tips-and-tricks/using-screenplay-markdown-with-marked">using that syntax in Marked</a>.</p><footer><strong>-Dan Frakes</strong> <cite><a href='http://www.macworld.com/article/164744/2012/01/marked_excels_at_previewing_markdown_and_html_documents.html'>Macworld</a></cite></footer></blockquote></p>

<p><a href="http://www.candlerblog.com/2011/12/08/screenplay-markdown-for-marked-is-here/">I love Screenplay Markdown</a> and couldn’t be happier to see it mentioned in Macworld. And they even gave Brett Terpstra’s awesome <a href="http://www.markedapp.com">Marked</a> app 4.5 mice. I’d give it 6.</p>

<p>(via <a href="http://www.macsparky.com/blog/2012/1/12/macworld-gives-marked-45-mice.html">David Sparks</a>.)</p>
